Azure Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) enable secure communication between Azure Virtual Networks and external networks such as on-premises datacenters or individual client devices over the public internet.

These connections use encryption (IPsec/IKE) to ensure data confidentiality and integrity during transmission.

Azure supports two primary VPN types:

* Site-to-Site (S2S): Connects entire on-premises networks to Azure
* Point-to-Site (P2S): Connects individual client devices to Azure

For example, an organization can connect its office network to Azure so employees can access cloud-hosted applications securely.

A real-life use case is remote workforce access, where employees connect to Azure resources from home using secure VPN connections.

Another example is hybrid cloud architecture, where part of the infrastructure remains on-premises while other components run in Azure.

Azure VPNs provide a cost-effective and secure connectivity solution.
